# 6. Project Testing Phase

## Testing Strategy
To ensure the reliability and accuracy of the Credit Card Approval Prediction System, the following testing approach will be implemented:

- Unit Testing: Individual components such as form validation in HTML templates and the backend logic in `app.py` will be tested to ensure they function as expected.
- Integration Testing: Verification that the frontend (HTML form) correctly communicates with the backend (Flask) and that the backend successfully loads and uses the `best_credit_model.pkl` file.
- Functional Testing: Ensuring that the application correctly processes user inputs and displays the appropriate "Approved" or "Rejected" result on the `result.html` page.

## Test Cases
| Test ID | Test Scenario | Expected Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| TC01 | Form Submission | Data is captured correctly and sent to the backend. |
| TC02 | Model Prediction | The model processes input and returns a valid prediction. |
| TC03 | UI Navigation | Users are redirected correctly from Home to Result page. |
| TC04 | Error Handling | System provides feedback if invalid or empty data is submitted. |

## Performance & Validation
- Accuracy Check: Validate if the model's prediction accuracy aligns with the training results.
- Responsiveness: Test the UI across different screen sizes to ensure it is user-friendly.
- Deployment Readiness: Ensure no bugs remain that could prevent the application from running in a live or local environment.
